# Notebook: 04_gold_star_schema
# Purpose : Build the final Gold Star Schema, consumed directly by BI tools.
#           Pure star schema — every dimension is fully denormalized (no
#           dimension-to-dimension relationships / no snowflaking).
#
# Dimensions (7):
#   1. gold.dim_date      — generated calendar dimension (2016-2021), not
#                            sourced from any file. Required for YTD vs LY
#                            YTD comparisons (business bonus question).
#   2. gold.dim_customer  — from silver.dim_customer, joined to
#                            silver.dim_division for the Division attribute
#                            (denormalized in, not a separate dim).
#   3. gold.dim_product   — from silver.dim_product, joined to
#                            silver.dim_category (category flattened in —
#                            this is what keeps the schema a pure star,
#                            not a snowflake).
#   4. gold.dim_employee  — from silver.dim_employee, joined to
#                            silver.dim_office (office attributes flattened in).
#   5. gold.dim_supplier  — from silver.dim_supplier, direct conform.
#   6. gold.dim_shipper   — from silver.dim_shipper, direct conform
#                            (includes the "Unknown Shipper" placeholder).
#   7. gold.dim_division  — from silver.dim_division, direct conform
#                            (kept standalone too, since Division is also
#                            one of the business dimensions requested
#                            independently in the case, e.g. "compare by
#                            Division" without going through Customer).
#
# Facts (2):
#   1. gold.fact_sales    — grain: one row per order line item
#                            (order_id, line_no). Built by joining
#                            silver.fact_order_details + silver.fact_orders
#                            + silver.fact_shipments (shipper_id and
#                            corrected shipment_date only — Shipments'
#                            other columns, e.g. its own customer_id/
#                            employee_id/product_id, are redundant with
#                            Orders/Order_Details and are NOT used, to
#                            avoid two sources of truth for the same fact).
#                            Measures: extended_amount (replaces the
#                            unusable Orders.TotalOrder) and margin,
#                            both calculated here — not stored redundantly
#                            upstream.
#   2. gold.fact_budget   — from silver.fact_budget, direct conform.
#
# Author  : Rafael
# Date    : 2026-07-15
